        "arabicTitle": "تراجعاً ملحوظاً في مؤشرات الشفافية في الإدارات العامة اللبنانية في العام 2021",
        "brief": "The percentage of public administrations that responded to Gherbal Initiative’s requests decreased in 2021 to about 42%, from 47% in 2020 and 52% in 2019. Noting that this percentage includes both negative and positive responses. Gherbal submitted official requests to obtain the lists of contractors with whom the administrations signed contracts over twenty years; from 2001 to 2020.  The lowest percentage of administrations’ complete responses over 4 years was recorded in 2021, as it did not exceed 14.8%, while it recorded 23.62% in 2020, 25.56% in 2019 and 16.8% in 2018. The year 2021 also recorded the lowest percentage; 21.68%, of administrations’ compliance with the legal time limit to respond to requests for information, while it scored 43.15% in 2020, 56.52% in 2019 and 54.54% in 2018.  The most prominent administrations that did not respond to Gherbal Initiative’s requests for the fourth year in a row are; the Parliament, the Lebanese Presidency and the Council of Ministers; for the former refused to respond to our request, and the latters stuck to their decision to refrain from providing Gherbal with any information.  The responses of some regulatory and judicial authorities were remarkable; where the State Council referred our request to the Court of Audi, while the latter’s response was incomplete and beyond the legal time limit, as well as the response of the Civil Service Board. Noting that the Central Inspection Bureau did not respond to our request at all.  In conclusion, the results of the 2021 report in comparison with the last three years, revealed a noticeable decline in terms of public administrations’ compliance to implement the provisions of the Access to Information Law, which is a negative indicator, especially after the issuance of the Law’s Implementation Decree and the recent amendment of the law itself.",
